<author><name><![CDATA[tepples]]></name></author>
<updated>2009-08-17T14:24:45-07:00</updated>
<published>2009-08-17T14:24:45-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5507&amp;p=49948#p49948</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5507&amp;p=49948#p49948"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Isolated Warrior 'special effects']]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5507&amp;p=49948#p49948"><![CDATA[
Isolated Warrior is TLROM, which has an MMC3 chip.<br /><br />The sinusoidal pattern is probably timed writes to the horizontal scroll register. The MMC3 scanline counter makes it easier: put in the number of the scanlines until the next time X is supposed to change, and the mapper will trigger an IRQ.<br /><br />Tearing apart is likewise writes to the scroll register, resetting the VRAM address . You can tell it's using the MMC3 scanline counter because a pattern repeats every 2 scanlines. (This mapper's counter can't trigger on successive lines.)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Mon Aug 17, 2009 2:24 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
