<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5507&amp;p=49946#p49946"><![CDATA[
I was playing through this game recently and was impressed by some of its special effects (not to mention that the game is a pretty solid isometric shooter in its own right).  There are two effects in particular that I wanted to point out.  <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WJiCi1f1SXE" class="postlink">This youtube clip</a> contains both:<br /><br />- Around 1:55, the background begins to move in a sinusoidal pattern.<br />- Around 4:05, the boss (which looks great) tears apart and seems to 'smear' the graphics between the two halves.<br /><br />So, any input on how these effects were achieved?  Any similar examples from other NES games?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2462">noattack</a> — Mon Aug 17, 2009 1:23 pm</p><hr />
